<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="52" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to Prime Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d52fn1">Sent to the White House Map Room; forwarded to
                                the United States Naval Attaché, London, via Navy
                            channels.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hyde
                                        Park</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-03">3 September 1944</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Number 616. Personal and top secret. From the President for the Prime
                                Minister.<note n="2" xml:id="d52fn2">For the portions of this
                                message omitted here, see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_229">p. 229</ref>.</note></p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>As to the exact employment of our forces in Italy in the future, this is
                            a matter we can discuss at <gloss target="#t_Octagon1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Octagon</hi></gloss>.…</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>